# adr-authoring-indexing-and-maintenance — History

## v1.3.0 (2026-06-30)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus issue #1452 — author 4 ADRs (0002–0005) + index +
structural guard.

**Verification:** verified-local (the 1.3.0 additions only; CI pending). The new
structural guard test was run and passed locally (4 passed) and `markdownlint-cli2`
passed; CI had not yet run when this entry was recorded. The skill's prior core content
remains verified-ci.

**What changed (minor bump 1.2.0 → 1.3.0 — additive, core workflow unchanged):**

- Added section I "Tracked-symbol anchoring, index membership guard, and the Nygard
  4-digit variant (Proposed — verified-local, CI pending)" to the Verified Workflow,
  covering:
  - The tracked-symbol anchoring rule: run `git ls-files <path>` before citing a code
    artifact as an ADR's canonical implementation; anchor on tracked symbols and demote
    untracked ones to illustrative.
  - The bidirectional README↔disk membership-guard test (asserts `linked == on_disk`
    set equality, plus filename regex, contiguous numbering, and required Nygard
    sections), with the `test_readme_index_lists_every_adr` pytest snippet.
  - The ProjectHephaestus Nygard 4-digit format variant (`docs/adr/NNNN-<kebab>.md`,
    `# ADR-NNNN:` title, list-style `- Status:` / `- Date:` / `- Tracks:` metadata,
    `## Alternatives considered` lowercase 'c', hook id `markdownlint-cli2`).
- Added 3 rows to the `## Failed Attempts` table: citing an untracked file as an ADR's
  canonical artifact; the one-directional ADR-index check; and trusting the audit's
  "dual-agent" characterization.
- Extended `description:` with triggers (8) tracked-artifact verification and (9)
  structural index guard.
- Bumped `version:` 1.2.0 → 1.3.0; `date:` → 2026-06-30; added tags `tracked-symbols`,
  `membership-guard`, `nygard-format`.

**Why:** In #1452 an ADR (0005) cited an untracked working-tree file
(`hephaestus/agents/invoker.py` / `AgentInvoker`) as its canonical artifact; `git ls-files`
returned empty and plan-review caught that the ADR would document a decision whose primary
artifact does not exist on `main`. This captures the tracked-vs-untracked anchoring rule,
the bidirectional index-sync guard pattern, the verify-the-audit's-characterization lesson
(audit said "dual-agent" but `runtime.py:23` had three), and the local Nygard 4-digit
format variant.

**Prior version:** v1.2.0 (2026-06-20). This history file retains the v1.0.0 entry and the
five original per-skill snapshots (doc-generate-adr, adr-index-entry,
adr-status-deferred-update, consolidate-duplicate-adr-references,
adr-directory-tree-accuracy) below; the v1.1.0/v1.2.0 increments were additive edits to the
canonical skill body rather than full snapshots.

